Author: Harshitha Onkar <honkar@openjdk.org>
Date: 2024-01-19 21:42:34 +0000
URL: https://git.openjdk.org/jdk/commit/f1b73350c237021c04ceac2f29f1f378630bd651

The original test fails intermittently when run multiple times on macOS 14.1, 14.2 without the fix. It used to pass when the whole CI job was run and used to fail at random attempt no. in the test. The test is stabilized and fixed by adding appropriate delays.

A pull request was submitted for review.
URL: https://git.openjdk.org/jdk/pull/17180
Date: 2023-12-21 20:33:53 +0000

on macOS14.2 it does still fail sometimes, but it also passes sometimes.
We should look to see if this is now just a test that needs some stabilisation.
I do however note that it was more reliable on 17u, so it would be nice to understand that too.
This is the only test observed so far that passes with jdk 17 on macOS 14 and fails on newer jdk versions 20, 21, 22.

Tested on macOS 14.1 GA on following JDK versions

jdk 17.0.9 - Pass
jdk 20.0.2 - Fails
jdk 22 - Fails
